findings.description:
`tygo.yaml` declares `typescript/config/src/generated.ts` is auto-generated from the Go `common` package, but the diff does NOT include any updates to `typescript/config/src/generated.ts` or `typescript/config/lib/generated.d.ts`. Both files still expose only the legacy fields:
  export interface FailsafeConfig { matchMethod?: string; matchFinality?: DataFinalityState[]; ... }
and have no `matchers?: MatcherConfig[]` field, no `MatcherConfig` interface, and no `MatcherAction` type. Consequences for downstream consumers of the `@erpc/config` TypeScript package: (1) cannot type-check or autocomplete the new `matchers: [...]` schema, which is the schema the new docs (`docs/pages/config/failsafe.mdx`, `docs/pages/config/matcher.mdx`) tell them to use â€” the TS examples in `failsafe.mdx` will fail `tsc` against the published types; (2) the legacy fields lack `@deprecated` JSDoc, so IDE tooling won't surface the migration; (3) any code that constructs a config via `createConfig({ ... })` with `matchers` is currently a type error.
